       </div> 
       <h3 id="repository"><a href="#repository">repository</a></h3> 
       <p>Activity related to a repository. The type of activity is specified in the <code>action</code> property of the payload object. For more information, see the "<a href="/en/rest/reference/repos">repositories</a>" REST API.</p> 
       <h4 id="availability-40"><a href="#availability-40">Availability</a></h4> 
       <ul> 
        <li>Repository webhooks receive all event types except <code>deleted</code></li> 
        <li>Organization webhooks</li> 
        <li>GitHub Apps with the <code>metadata</code> permission receive all event types except <code>deleted</code></li> 
       </ul> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-object-38"><a href="#webhook-payload-object-38">Webhook payload object</a></h4> 
       <table>
        <thead>
         <tr>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
         </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
         <tr>
          <td><code>action</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The action that was performed. This can be one of:
           <ul>
            <li><code>created</code> - A repository is created.</li>
            <li><code>deleted</code> - A repository is deleted.</li>
            <li><code>archived</code> - A repository is archived.</li>
            <li><code>unarchived</code> - A repository is unarchived.</li>
            <li><code>edited</code> - A repository's information is edited.</li>
            <li><code>renamed</code> - A repository is renamed.</li>
            <li><code>transferred</code> - A repository is transferred.</li>
            <li><code>publicized</code> - A repository is made public.</li>
            <li> <code>privatized</code> - A repository is made private.</li>
           </ul></td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>repository</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The <a href="/en/rest/reference/repos#get-a-repository"><code>repository</code></a> where the event occurred.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>organization</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>Webhook payloads contain the <a href="/en/rest/reference/orgs#get-an-organization"><code>organization</code></a> object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>installation</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The GitHub App installation. Webhook payloads contain the <code>installation</code> property when the event is configured for and sent to a GitHub App.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>sender</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The user that triggered the event.</td>
         </tr>
        </tbody>
       </table>

       <div class="height-constrained-code-block">

       </div> 
       <h3 id="repository_import"><a href="#repository_import">repository_import</a></h3> 
       <p>Activity related to a repository being imported to GitHub. The type of activity is specified in the <code>action</code> property of the payload object. For more information, see the "<a href="/en/rest/reference/migrations#source-imports">source imports</a>" REST API. To receive this event for a personal repository, you must create an empty repository prior to the import. This event can be triggered using either the <a href="/en/articles/importing-a-repository-with-github-importer">GitHub Importer</a> or the <a href="/en/rest/reference/migrations#source-imports">Source imports API</a>.</p> 
       <h4 id="availability-41"><a href="#availability-41">Availability</a></h4> 
       <ul> 
        <li>Repository webhooks</li> 
        <li>Organization webhooks</li> 
       </ul> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-object-39"><a href="#webhook-payload-object-39">Webhook payload object</a></h4> 
       <table>
        <thead>
         <tr>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
         </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
         <tr>
          <td><code>status</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The final state of the import. This can be one of <code>success</code>, <code>cancelled</code>, or <code>failure</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>repository</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The <a href="/en/rest/reference/repos#get-a-repository"><code>repository</code></a> where the event occurred.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>organization</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>Webhook payloads contain the <a href="/en/rest/reference/orgs#get-an-organization"><code>organization</code></a> object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>sender</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The user that triggered the event.</td>
         </tr>
        </tbody>
       </table> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-example-39"><a href="#webhook-payload-example-39">Webhook payload example</a></h4>

    <span class="hljs-attr">"issues_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/orgs/Octocoders/issues"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"members_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/orgs/Octocoders/members{/member}"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"public_members_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/orgs/Octocoders/public_members{/member}"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"avatar_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/38302899?v=4"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"description"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">""</span>
  },

    <span class="hljs-attr">"login"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"Codertocat"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"id"</span>: <span class="hljs-number">21031067</span>,

       </div> 
       <h3 id="repository_vulnerability_alert"><a href="#repository_vulnerability_alert">repository_vulnerability_alert</a></h3> 
       <p>Activity related to security vulnerability alerts in a repository. The type of activity is specified in the <code>action</code> property of the payload object. For more information, see the "<a href="/en/github/managing-security-vulnerabilities/about-alerts-for-vulnerable-dependencies">About alerts for vulnerable dependencies</a>".</p> 
       <h4 id="availability-42"><a href="#availability-42">Availability</a></h4> 
       <ul> 
        <li>Repository webhooks</li> 
        <li>Organization webhooks</li> 
       </ul> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-object-40"><a href="#webhook-payload-object-40">Webhook payload object</a></h4> 
       <table>
        <thead>
         <tr>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
         </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
         <tr>
          <td><code>action</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The action that was performed. This can be one of <code>create</code>, <code>dismiss</code>, or <code>resolve</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>alert</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The security alert of the vulnerable dependency.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>repository</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The <a href="/en/rest/reference/repos#get-a-repository"><code>repository</code></a> where the event occurred.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>organization</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>Webhook payloads contain the <a href="/en/rest/reference/orgs#get-an-organization"><code>organization</code></a> object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>sender</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The user that triggered the event.</td>
         </tr>
        </tbody>
       </table> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-example-40"><a href="#webhook-payload-example-40">Webhook payload example</a></h4>

       <h3 id="secret_scanning_alert"><a href="#secret_scanning_alert">secret_scanning_alert</a></h3> 
       <p>Activity related to secret scanning alerts in a repository. The type of activity is specified in the action property of the payload object. For more information, see <a href="/en/github/administering-a-repository/about-secret-scanning">About secret scanning</a>.</p> 
       <h4 id="availability-43"><a href="#availability-43">Availability</a></h4> 
       <ul> 
        <li>Repository webhooks</li> 
        <li>Organization webhooks</li> 
        <li>GitHub Apps with the <code>secret_scanning_alerts:read</code> permission</li> 
       </ul> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-object-41"><a href="#webhook-payload-object-41">Webhook payload object</a></h4> 
       <table>
        <thead>
         <tr>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
         </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
         <tr>
          <td><code>action</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The action that was performed. This can be either <code>created</code>, <code>resolved</code>, or <code>reopened</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>alert</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The secret scanning alert involved in the event.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>repository</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The <a href="/en/rest/reference/repos#get-a-repository"><code>repository</code></a> where the event occurred.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>organization</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>Webhook payloads contain the <a href="/en/rest/reference/orgs#get-an-organization"><code>organization</code></a> object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>installation</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The GitHub App installation. Webhook payloads contain the <code>installation</code> property when the event is configured for and sent to a GitHub App.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>sender</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>If the <code>action</code> is <code>resolved</code> or <code>reopened</code>, the <code>sender</code> object will be the user that triggered the event. The <code>sender</code> object is empty for all other actions.</td>
         </tr>
        </tbody>
       </table> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-example-41"><a href="#webhook-payload-example-41">Webhook payload example</a></h4> 
       <div class="height-constrained-code-block"> 
        <pre><code class="hljs language-json">{
  <span class="hljs-attr">"action"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"reopened"</span>,
  <span class="hljs-attr">"alert"</span>: {
    <span class="hljs-attr">"number"</span>: <span class="hljs-number">191</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"secret_type"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"adafruit_io_key"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"resolution"</span>: <span class="hljs-literal">null</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"resolved_by"</span>: <span class="hljs-literal">null</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"resolved_at"</span>: <span class="hljs-literal">null</span>
  },
  <span class="hljs-attr">"repository"</span>: {
    <span class="hljs-attr">"id"</span>: <span class="hljs-number">257423561</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"node_id"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnkyNTc0MjM1NjE="</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"name"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"Hello-World"</span>,

       <h3 id="security_advisory"><a href="#security_advisory">security_advisory</a></h3> 
       <p>Activity related to a security advisory. A security advisory provides information about security-related vulnerabilities in software on GitHub. The security advisory dataset also powers the GitHub security alerts, see "<a href="/en/github/managing-security-vulnerabilities/about-alerts-for-vulnerable-dependencies">About alerts for vulnerable dependencies</a>."</p> 
       <h4 id="availability-44"><a href="#availability-44">Availability</a></h4> 
       <ul> 
        <li>GitHub Apps with the <code>security_events</code> permission</li> 
       </ul> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-object-42"><a href="#webhook-payload-object-42">Webhook payload object</a></h4> 
       <table>
        <thead>
         <tr>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
         </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
         <tr>
          <td><code>action</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The action that was performed. The action can be one of <code>published</code>, <code>updated</code>, or <code>performed</code> for all new events.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>security_advisory</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The details of the security advisory, including summary, description, and severity.</td>
         </tr>
        </tbody>
       </table> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-example-42"><a href="#webhook-payload-example-42">Webhook payload example</a></h4> 
       <div class="height-constrained-code-block"> 
        <pre><code class="hljs language-json">{
  <span class="hljs-attr">"action"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"published"</span>,
  <span class="hljs-attr">"security_advisory"</span>: {
    <span class="hljs-attr">"ghsa_id"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"GHSA-rf4j-j272-fj86"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"summary"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"Moderate severity vulnerability that affects django"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"description"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"django.contrib.auth.forms.AuthenticationForm in Django 2.0 before 2.0.2, and 1.11.8 and 1.11.9, allows remote attackers to obtain potentially sensitive information by leveraging data exposure from the confirm_login_allowed() method, as demonstrated by discovering whether a user account is inactive."</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"severity"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"moderate"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"identifiers"</span>: [
      {
        <span class="hljs-attr">"value"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"GHSA-rf4j-j272-fj86"</span>,
        <span class="hljs-attr">"type"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"GHSA"</span>
      },
      {
        <span class="hljs-attr">"value"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"CVE-2018-6188"</span>,
        <span class="hljs-attr">"type"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"CVE"</span>
      }
    ],
    <span class="hljs-attr">"references"</span>: [
      {
        <span class="hljs-attr">"url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2018-6188"</span>
      }
    ],
    <span class="hljs-attr">"published_at"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"2018-10-03T21:13:54Z"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"updated_at"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"2018-10-03T21:13:54Z"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"withdrawn_at"</span>: <span class="hljs-literal">null</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"vulnerabilities"</span>: [
      {
        <span class="hljs-attr">"package"</span>: {
          <span class="hljs-attr">"ecosystem"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"pip"</span>,
          <span class="hljs-attr">"name"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"django"</span>
        },
        <span class="hljs-attr">"severity"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"moderate"</span>,
        <span class="hljs-attr">"vulnerable_version_range"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"&gt;= 2.0.0, &lt; 2.0.2"</span>,
        <span class="hljs-attr">"first_patched_version"</span>: {
          <span class="hljs-attr">"identifier"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"2.0.2"</span>
        }
      },
      {
        <span class="hljs-attr">"package"</span>: {
          <span class="hljs-attr">"ecosystem"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"pip"</span>,
          <span class="hljs-attr">"name"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"django"</span>
        },
        <span class="hljs-attr">"severity"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"moderate"</span>,
        <span class="hljs-attr">"vulnerable_version_range"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"&gt;= 1.11.8, &lt; 1.11.10"</span>,
        <span class="hljs-attr">"first_patched_version"</span>: {
          <span class="hljs-attr">"identifier"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"1.11.10"</span>
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
</code></pre> 
       </div> 
       <h3 id="sponsorship"><a href="#sponsorship">sponsorship</a></h3> 
       <p>Activity related to a sponsorship listing. The type of activity is specified in the <code>action</code> property of the payload object. For more information, see "<a href="/en/sponsors/getting-started-with-github-sponsors/about-github-sponsors">About GitHub Sponsors</a>".</p> 
       <p>You can only create a sponsorship webhook on GitHub. For more information, see "<a href="/en/sponsors/integrating-with-github-sponsors/configuring-webhooks-for-events-in-your-sponsored-account">Configuring webhooks for events in your sponsored account</a>".</p> 
       <h4 id="availability-45"><a href="#availability-45">Availability</a></h4> 
       <ul> 
        <li>Sponsored accounts</li> 
       </ul> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-object-43"><a href="#webhook-payload-object-43">Webhook payload object</a></h4> 
       <table>
        <thead>
         <tr>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
         </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
         <tr>
          <td><code>action</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The action that was performed. This can be one of <code>created</code>, <code>cancelled</code>, <code>edited</code>, <code>tier_changed</code>, <code>pending_cancellation</code>, or <code>pending_tier_change</code>. Note: The <code>created</code> action is only triggered after payment is processed.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>effective_date</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The <code>pending_cancellation</code> and <code>pending_tier_change</code> event types will include the date the cancellation or tier change will take effect.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>changes[tier][from]</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The <code>tier_changed</code> and <code>pending_tier_change</code> will include the original tier before the change or pending change. For more information, see the <a href="/en/webhooks/event-payloads#webhook-payload-example-when-someone-downgrades-a-sponsorship">pending tier change payload</a>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>changes[privacy_level][from]</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The <code>edited</code> event types include the details about the change when someone edits a sponsorship to change the privacy.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>sender</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The user that triggered the event.</td>
         </tr>
        </tbody>
       </table> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-example-when-someone-creates-a-sponsorship"><a href="#webhook-payload-example-when-someone-creates-a-sponsorship">Webhook payload example when someone creates a sponsorship</a></h4> 
       <div class="height-constrained-code-block"> 
        <pre><code class="hljs language-json">{
  <span class="hljs-attr">"action"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"created"</span>,
  <span class="hljs-attr">"sponsorship"</span>: {
    <span class="hljs-attr">"node_id"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"MDExOlNwb25zb3JzaGlwMQ=="</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"created_at"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"2019-12-20T19:24:46+00:00"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"sponsorable"</span>: {
      <span class="hljs-attr">"login"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"octocat"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"id"</span>: <span class="hljs-number">5</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"node_id"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"MDQ6VXNlcjU="</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"avatar_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/5?"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"gravatar_id"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">""</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/users/octocat"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"html_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://github.com/octocat"</span>,

       <h3 id="star"><a href="#star">star</a></h3> 
       <p>Activity related to a repository being starred. The type of activity is specified in the <code>action</code> property of the payload object. For more information, see the "<a href="/en/rest/reference/activity#starring">starring</a>" REST API.</p> 
       <h4 id="availability-46"><a href="#availability-46">Availability</a></h4> 
       <ul> 
        <li>Repository webhooks</li> 
        <li>Organization webhooks</li> 
       </ul> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-object-44"><a href="#webhook-payload-object-44">Webhook payload object</a></h4> 
       <table>
        <thead>
         <tr>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
         </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
         <tr>
          <td><code>action</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The action performed. Can be <code>created</code> or <code>deleted</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>starred_at</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The time the star was created. This is a timestamp in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601">ISO 8601</a> format: <code>YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ</code>. Will be <code>null</code> for the <code>deleted</code> action.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>repository</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The <a href="/en/rest/reference/repos#get-a-repository"><code>repository</code></a> where the event occurred.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>organization</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>Webhook payloads contain the <a href="/en/rest/reference/orgs#get-an-organization"><code>organization</code></a> object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>sender</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The user that triggered the event.</td>
         </tr>
        </tbody>
       </table> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-example-43"><a href="#webhook-payload-example-43">Webhook payload example</a></h4> 
       <div class="height-constrained-code-block"> 
        <pre><code class="hljs language-json">{
  <span class="hljs-attr">"action"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"created"</span>,
  <span class="hljs-attr">"starred_at"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"2019-05-15T15:20:40Z"</span>,
  <span class="hljs-attr">"repository"</span>: {
    <span class="hljs-attr">"id"</span>: <span class="hljs-number">186853002</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"node_id"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnkxODY4NTMwMDI="</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"name"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"Hello-World"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"full_name"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"Codertocat/Hello-World"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"private"</span>: <span class="hljs-literal">false</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"owner"</span>: {
      <span class="hljs-attr">"login"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"Codertocat"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"id"</span>: <span class="hljs-number">21031067</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"node_id"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"MDQ6VXNlcjIxMDMxMDY3"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"avatar_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/21031067?v=4"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"gravatar_id"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">""</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/users/Codertocat"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"html_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://github.com/Codertocat"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"followers_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/users/Codertocat/followers"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"following_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/users/Codertocat/following{/other_user}"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"gists_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/users/Codertocat/gists{/gist_id}"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"starred_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/users/Codertocat/starred{/owner}{/repo}"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"subscriptions_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/users/Codertocat/subscriptions"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"organizations_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/users/Codertocat/orgs"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"repos_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/users/Codertocat/repos"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"events_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/users/Codertocat/events{/privacy}"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"received_events_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/users/Codertocat/received_events"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"type"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"User"</span>,
      <span class="hljs-attr">"site_admin"</span>: <span class="hljs-literal">false</span>
    },
    <span class="hljs-attr">"html_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://github.com/Codertocat/Hello-World"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"description"</span>: <span class="hljs-literal">null</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"fork"</span>: <span class="hljs-literal">false</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/repos/Codertocat/Hello-World"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"forks_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/repos/Codertocat/Hello-World/forks"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"keys_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/repos/Codertocat/Hello-World/keys{/key_id}"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"collaborators_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/repos/Codertocat/Hello-World/collaborators{/collaborator}"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"teams_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/repos/Codertocat/Hello-World/teams"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"hooks_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/repos/Codertocat/Hello-World/hooks"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"issue_events_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/repos/Codertocat/Hello-World/issues/events{/number}"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"events_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/repos/Codertocat/Hello-World/events"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"assignees_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/repos/Codertocat/Hello-World/assignees{/user}"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"branches_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/repos/Codertocat/Hello-World/branches{/branch}"</span>,
    <span class="hljs-attr">"tags_url"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"https://api.github.com/repos/Codertocat/Hello-World/tags"</span>,

       </div> 
       <h3 id="status"><a href="#status">status</a></h3> 
       <p>When the status of a Git commit changes. The type of activity is specified in the <code>action</code> property of the payload object. For more information, see the "<a href="/en/rest/reference/repos#statuses">statuses</a>" REST API.</p> 
       <h4 id="availability-47"><a href="#availability-47">Availability</a></h4> 
       <ul> 
        <li>Repository webhooks</li> 
        <li>Organization webhooks</li> 
        <li>GitHub Apps with the <code>statuses</code> permission</li> 
       </ul> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-object-45"><a href="#webhook-payload-object-45">Webhook payload object</a></h4> 
       <table>
        <thead>
         <tr>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
         </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
         <tr>
          <td><code>id</code></td>
          <td><code>integer</code></td>
          <td>The unique identifier of the status.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>sha</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The Commit SHA.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>state</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The new state. Can be <code>pending</code>, <code>success</code>, <code>failure</code>, or <code>error</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>description</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The optional human-readable description added to the status.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>target_url</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The optional link added to the status.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>branches</code></td>
          <td><code>array</code></td>
          <td>An array of branch objects containing the status' SHA. Each branch contains the given SHA, but the SHA may or may not be the head of the branch. The array includes a maximum of 10 branches.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>repository</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The <a href="/en/rest/reference/repos#get-a-repository"><code>repository</code></a> where the event occurred.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>organization</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>Webhook payloads contain the <a href="/en/rest/reference/orgs#get-an-organization"><code>organization</code></a> object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>installation</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The GitHub App installation. Webhook payloads contain the <code>installation</code> property when the event is configured for and sent to a GitHub App.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>sender</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The user that triggered the event.</td>
         </tr>
        </tbody>
       </table>

       <h3 id="team"><a href="#team">team</a></h3> 
       <p>Activity related to an organization's team. The type of activity is specified in the <code>action</code> property of the payload object. For more information, see the "<a href="/en/rest/reference/teams">teams</a>" REST API.</p> 
       <h4 id="availability-48"><a href="#availability-48">Availability</a></h4> 
       <ul> 
        <li>Organization webhooks</li> 
        <li>GitHub Apps with the <code>members</code> permission</li> 
       </ul> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-object-46"><a href="#webhook-payload-object-46">Webhook payload object</a></h4> 
       <table>
        <thead>
         <tr>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
         </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
         <tr>
          <td><code>action</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The action that was performed. Can be one of <code>created</code>, <code>deleted</code>, <code>edited</code>, <code>added_to_repository</code>, or <code>removed_from_repository</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>team</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The team itself.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>changes</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The changes to the team if the action was <code>edited</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>changes[description][from]</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The previous version of the description if the action was <code>edited</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>changes[name][from]</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The previous version of the name if the action was <code>edited</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>changes[privacy][from]</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The previous version of the team's privacy if the action was <code>edited</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>changes[repository][permissions][from][admin]</code></td>
          <td><code>boolean</code></td>
          <td>The previous version of the team member's <code>admin</code> permission on a repository, if the action was <code>edited</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>changes[repository][permissions][from][pull]</code></td>
          <td><code>boolean</code></td>
          <td>The previous version of the team member's <code>pull</code> permission on a repository, if the action was <code>edited</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>changes[repository][permissions][from][push]</code></td>
          <td><code>boolean</code></td>
          <td>The previous version of the team member's <code>push</code> permission on a repository, if the action was <code>edited</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>repository</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The repository that was added or removed from to the team's purview if the action was <code>added_to_repository</code>, <code>removed_from_repository</code>, or <code>edited</code>. For <code>edited</code> actions, <code>repository</code> also contains the team's new permission levels for the repository.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>organization</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>Webhook payloads contain the <a href="/en/rest/reference/orgs#get-an-organization"><code>organization</code></a> object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>sender</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The user that triggered the event.</td>
         </tr>
        </tbody>
       </table> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-example-45"><a href="#webhook-payload-example-45">Webhook payload example</a></h4> 
       <div class="height-constrained-code-block"> 
        <pre><code class="hljs language-json">{

       <h3 id="team_add"><a href="#team_add">team_add</a></h3> 
       <p>When a <a href="/en/rest/reference/teams#add-or-update-team-repository-permissions">repository is added to a team</a>.</p> 
       <h4 id="availability-49"><a href="#availability-49">Availability</a></h4> 
       <ul> 
        <li>Repository webhooks</li> 
        <li>Organization webhooks</li> 
        <li>GitHub Apps with the <code>members</code> permission</li> 
       </ul> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-object-47"><a href="#webhook-payload-object-47">Webhook payload object</a></h4> 
       <table>
        <thead>
         <tr>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
         </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
         <tr>
          <td><code>team</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The <a href="/en/rest/reference/teams">team</a> that was modified. <strong>Note:</strong> Older events may not include this in the payload.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>repository</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The <a href="/en/rest/reference/repos#get-a-repository"><code>repository</code></a> where the event occurred.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>organization</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>Webhook payloads contain the <a href="/en/rest/reference/orgs#get-an-organization"><code>organization</code></a> object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>installation</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The GitHub App installation. Webhook payloads contain the <code>installation</code> property when the event is configured for and sent to a GitHub App.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>sender</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The user that triggered the event.</td>
         </tr>
        </tbody>
       </table> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-example-46"><a href="#webhook-payload-example-46">Webhook payload example</a></h4> 
       <div class="height-constrained-code-block"> 
        <pre><code class="hljs language-json">{

       </div> 
       <h3 id="watch"><a href="#watch">watch</a></h3> 
       <p>When someone stars a repository. The type of activity is specified in the <code>action</code> property of the payload object. For more information, see the "<a href="/en/rest/reference/activity#starring">starring</a>" REST API.</p> 
       <p>The events actor is the <a href="/en/rest/reference/users">user</a> who starred a repository, and the events repository is the <a href="/en/rest/reference/repos">repository</a> that was starred.</p> 
       <h4 id="availability-50"><a href="#availability-50">Availability</a></h4> 
       <ul> 
        <li>Repository webhooks</li> 
        <li>Organization webhooks</li> 
        <li>GitHub Apps with the <code>metadata</code> permission</li> 
       </ul> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-object-48"><a href="#webhook-payload-object-48">Webhook payload object</a></h4> 
       <table>
        <thead>
         <tr>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
         </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
         <tr>
          <td><code>action</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The action that was performed. Currently, can only be <code>started</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>repository</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The <a href="/en/rest/reference/repos#get-a-repository"><code>repository</code></a> where the event occurred.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>organization</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>Webhook payloads contain the <a href="/en/rest/reference/orgs#get-an-organization"><code>organization</code></a> object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>installation</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The GitHub App installation. Webhook payloads contain the <code>installation</code> property when the event is configured for and sent to a GitHub App.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>sender</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The user that triggered the event.</td>
         </tr>
        </tbody>
       </table>

       <h3 id="workflow_dispatch"><a href="#workflow_dispatch">workflow_dispatch</a></h3> 
       <p>This event occurs when someone triggers a workflow run on GitHub or sends a <code>POST</code> request to the "<a href="/en/rest/reference/actions/#create-a-workflow-dispatch-event">Create a workflow dispatch event</a>" endpoint. For more information, see "<a href="/en/actions/reference/events-that-trigger-workflows#workflow_dispatch">Events that trigger workflows</a>."</p> 
       <h4 id="availability-51"><a href="#availability-51">Availability</a></h4> 
       <ul> 
        <li>GitHub Apps must have the <code>contents</code> permission to receive this webhook.</li> 
       </ul> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-example-48"><a href="#webhook-payload-example-48">Webhook payload example</a></h4> 
       <div class="height-constrained-code-block"> 
        <pre><code class="hljs language-json">{
  <span class="hljs-attr">"inputs"</span>: {
    <span class="hljs-attr">"name"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"Mona the Octocat"</span>
  },
  <span class="hljs-attr">"ref"</span>: <span class="hljs-string">"refs/heads/master"</span>,
  <span class="hljs-attr">"repository"</span>: {
    <span class="hljs-attr">"id"</span>: <span class="hljs-number">17273051</span>,

       <h3 id="workflow_run"><a href="#workflow_run">workflow_run</a></h3> 
       <p>When a GitHub Actions workflow run is requested or completed. For more information, see "<a href="/en/actions/reference/events-that-trigger-workflows#workflow_run">Events that trigger workflows</a>."</p> 
       <h4 id="availability-52"><a href="#availability-52">Availability</a></h4> 
       <ul> 
        <li>GitHub Apps with the <code>actions</code> or <code>contents</code> permissions.</li> 
       </ul> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-object-49"><a href="#webhook-payload-object-49">Webhook payload object</a></h4> 
       <table>
        <thead>
         <tr>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
         </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
         <tr>
          <td><code>action</code></td>
          <td><code>string</code></td>
          <td>The action that was performed. Can be one of <code>requested</code> or <code>completed</code>.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>workflow_run</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The workflow run. Many <code>workflow_run</code> keys, such as <code>head_branch</code>, <code>conclusion</code>, and <code>pull_requests</code> are the same as those in a <a href="#check_suite"><code>check_suite</code></a> object.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>workflow</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The workflow that generated the workflow run.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>organization</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>Webhook payloads contain the <a href="/en/rest/reference/orgs#get-an-organization"><code>organization</code></a> object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>repository</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The <a href="/en/rest/reference/repos#get-a-repository"><code>repository</code></a> where the event occurred.</td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
          <td><code>sender</code></td>
          <td><code>object</code></td>
          <td>The user that triggered the event.</td>
         </tr>
        </tbody>
       </table> 
       <h4 id="webhook-payload-example-49"><a href="#webhook-payload-example-49">Webhook payload example</a></h4> 
       <div class="height-constrained-code-block">
